&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a band 2 Maternity Support Worker (admin) to work 11.25 hours per week to meet the needs of the maternity service. Post is permanent at Welshpool Birth centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide administrative support by working closely with the team of Midwives and maintaining stock levels within the Birth Centre. This is a varied role and the need for flexibility and adaptability is essential. This is a front of house role which meets and greets our clients and their families entering the Birth Centre or via the telephone therefore a professional manner and excellent communication skills are essential alongside administration experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a service with one of the highest home birth rates in Wales, a high physiological birth rate and the highest breastfeeding rate in Wales. As a service, we are passionate about supporting ongoing professional development and the opportunity to access an award-winning training during your employment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh for this post is desirable; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
